Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Porträt"

- First subfolder (Annotation: "Rubens Büste von Georg Petel") addressed (inside) to "Herrn Prof. Dr. H. Evers 6101 Traisa b. Darmstadt Waldstr. 43" and dated 13.10.1967:
    - Photos and negatives of Rubens bust by G. Petel
- Second subfolder:
    - Photos of portraits of Rubens and Rubens' mother
- Photos of portraits of Rubens, Rubens' family, etc.
- Correspondence with Hans Rudolph dated 1951
- Third subfolder (Annotation: "XII der "träumende Silen" Wiener Akademie von Rubens")
(Empty)
- Photos of portraits of Rubens, Rubens' family, etc.
- Paper cover (Annotation: "IV Herzog Lerma"):
    - Reproduction of the 'Equestrian Portrait of the Duke of Lerma'
    - Notes about the 'Equestrian Portrait of the Duke of Lerma'
    - Draft text "Herzog Lerma"
- Extracts from different publications
- Notes about Rubens' artworks in Vienna dated 1967
